<body>
  <h1>MARA Holdings, Inc. - Form 8-K</h1>
  <h2>August 14, 2024 - Bitcoin Treasury Purchase Announcement</h2>
  
  <section id="filing-info">
    <p><strong>SEC Accession Number:</strong> 0001493152-24-032433</p>
    <p><strong>Filing Date:</strong> August 14, 2024</p>
    <p><strong>Period of Report:</strong> August 14, 2024</p>
    <p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1507605/000149315224032433/ex99-1.htm">SEC EDGAR EX-99.1</a></p>
  </section>

  <section id="summary">
    <h3>Summary</h3>
    <p>Marathon Digital Holdings, Inc. announced the closing of its $300 million offering of 2.125% 
    convertible senior notes due 2031 and the use of proceeds to purchase bitcoin.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="holdings">
    <h3>Bitcoin Purchase Details</h3>
    <p><strong>Purchase Period:</strong> August 12, 2024 to August 14, 2024</p>
    <p><strong>Bitcoin Acquired:</strong> Approximately <strong>4,144 BTC</strong></p>
    <p><strong>Total Cost:</strong> Approximately <strong>$249 million</strong> in cash</p>
    <p><strong>Average Price:</strong> Approximately <strong>$59,500 per bitcoin</strong> (inclusive of fees and expenses)</p>
    <p><strong>Source of Funds:</strong> Proceeds from the sale of 2.125% convertible senior notes due 2031</p>
    
    <p><em>From the 8-K: "On August 14, 2024, MARA also announced that, during the period between 
    August 12, 2024 and August 14, 2024, MARA acquired approximately 4,144 bitcoin for approximately 
    $249 million in cash, using proceeds from the sale of the notes, at an average price of 
    approximately $59,500 per bitcoin, inclusive of fees and expenses."</em></p>
  </section>

  <section id="context">
    <h3>Treasury Strategy Context</h3>
    <p>This filing marks the beginning of MARA's aggressive bitcoin treasury strategy. Prior to this 
    purchase, MARA held approximately 18,488 BTC as of June 30, 2024 (per Q2 2024 10-Q). After this 
    purchase, holdings increased to approximately 22,632 BTC.</p>
    <p>MARA stated: "MARA intends to use the remaining net proceeds from the sale of the notes to 
    acquire additional bitcoin and for general corporate purposes, which may include working capital, 
    strategic acquisitions, expansion of existing assets, and repayment of debt and other outstanding 
    obligations."</p>
  </section>

  <section id="notes-details">
    <h3>Convertible Notes Details</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Principal Amount:</strong> $300 million (includes $50M from option exercise)</li>
      <li><strong>Interest Rate:</strong> 2.125% per annum, payable semi-annually</li>
      <li><strong>Maturity:</strong> September 1, 2031</li>
      <li><strong>Initial Conversion Price:</strong> Approximately $18.89 per share</li>
      <li><strong>Net Proceeds:</strong> Approximately $292.5 million</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
